---
description: Agent-persona dispatch — main agent delegates ALL file I/O to sub-agents
alwaysApply: true
---

**CRITICAL — Response ordering for web platform:**
On this platform, only the text AFTER your last tool call is visible to the user. All text before tool calls is hidden. Therefore:
1. Do ALL tool calls first (per-turn-check, sub-agents, knowledge queries, any work).
2. Output your entire response as the LAST thing — after all tool calls are complete.
3. Never output response text before a tool call — it will be hidden from the user.

---

**No file I/O:** Main agent NEVER uses Read, Write, StrReplace, Glob, Grep, or SemanticSearch directly. ALL file I/O delegated to sub-agents (generalPurpose). Shell for non-file commands is fine.

**Tasks:** `agent-persona/tasks/<name>/` — run `task.sh` via Shell → follow `spawn:` instruction (sub-agent reads task.md, runs pre.sh/post.sh itself).

- **Start of every turn:** `bash agent-persona/tasks/per-turn-check/task.sh --turn N --message "<user message>"` where N is the turn number (0 for first turn, 1+ after). This is your ONLY startup call each turn.
- **End-of-day:** User done for day → `bash agent-persona/tasks/prepare-handoff/task.sh --end-of-day`.
- **Personality:** User wants different tone → `bash agent-persona/tasks/apply-personality/task.sh --words "<user's words>"`.
- **Knowledge:** Need past decisions → `bash agent-persona/tasks/query-knowledge/task.sh --query "<query>"`.
- **Initiative:** After substantial work → check `agent-persona/data/learned_triggers.json` for `task_complete` triggers.
- **Debug:** "debug on/off" → `bash agent-persona/tasks/toggle-debug/task.sh on|off`.
- **Conversations:** "save/load/new/list convo" or "add main thread" → `bash agent-persona/tasks/manage-conversation/task.sh --action <action> [--name <name>] [--summary "<summary>"]`. For fork-main: `--action fork-main` (no --name needed).
- **Living docs:** "create/update/show/read/list doc" → `bash agent-persona/tasks/manage-living-doc/task.sh --action <action> --name <name> [--summary "<summary>"]`.
- **Backlog:** "add/show/done/update backlog" → `bash agent-persona/scripts/backlog.sh <subcommand> [--title "..." --category ... --priority ...]`.
- **Forgetting:** "pin/unpin/forget/decay status/surface/restore/show archive" → `bash agent-persona/scripts/forgetting.sh <subcommand> [<index>] [--category <cat>] [--limit <n>]`.
- **Help:** "help" / "commands" → print summary from `agent-persona/commands.md`.
- **Footer:** handled inline — per-turn-check provides the footer timestamp ("Your LAST line of response must be: — HH:MM —"). Do NOT call footer.sh.
- **Agent ops:** `agent-persona/scripts/update.sh` · `agent-persona/scripts/export-to-project.sh` via Shell.
